{"content":"Decision: Validate max_concurrent >= 1 with explicit ValueError

If max_concurrent < 1, raise ValueError immediately before creating any tasks.

Why: asyncio.Semaphore(0) would deadlock — no task could ever acquire it. asyncio.Semaphore with a negative value raises ValueError from the Semaphore constructor, but validating before any infrastructure is set up makes the contract explicit and the error clearer to callers.","wing":"cancel-async-tasks","room":"run","importance":2,"source":"session: implementing run_tasks in run.py"}

